    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "makes sense. we're also worried about the weave being too open and letting things through. like, if the density isn't high enough, could imperfections or tiny gaps in the fabric structure cause issues with the \"barrier\" aspect of the textile, or is that just overthinking it?",
      "source": "evaluator",
